parameters.query:
select distinct u.uuid, A.listings as overall_listings, count(distinct l.id)as listings
from listings l
left join users u on u.id = l.user_id
left join (select distinct listing_id, country, city_id from listing_location) ll on ll.listing_id = l.id
--
left join
(select distinct u.uuid, count(distinct l.id)as listings
from listings l
left join (select distinct listing_id, country, city_id from listing_location) ll on ll.listing_id = l.id
left join users u on u.id = l.user_id
where l.status = 'approved'
and ll.country = 'Malaysia'
group by 1)A
on A.uuid = u.uuid
where ll.country = 'Malaysia'
and l.status = 'approved'
and l.approved_at > CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '15 Minutes'
and A.listings <= '1'
group by 1,2
